Notes.[note 1]: These figures have been revised following receipt of Gosport's Q4 2021 to 2022 data.
Notes.[r1]: This indicates that an authority has revised a previous submission which has resulted in amended figures to the April to June 2022 figures in comparison to the previous publication.
Notes.[r2]: This indicates that an authority has revised a previous submission which has resulted in amended figures to the July to September 2022 figures in comparison to the previous publication.
Notes.[r3]: This indicates that an authority has revised a previous submission which has resulted in amended figures to the October to December 2022 figures in comparison to the previous publication.
Notes.[r]: This indicates that data has been revised.
Notes.[x]: This indicates that data is not available or has been suppressed. Refer to the notes column in each worksheet for further information.
Notes.[z]: This indicates that an authority did not exist in the period. Local authority reorganisation is usually as a result of structural changes to local government, for example where local districts merge to become a unitary authority.
